Preliminaries

Loading data

exec_lhq <- as.data.table(fread("subjectdata/axcpt_lhq_data_forpub.csv"))
axcpt <- as.data.table(fread("rawdata/axcpt_trial_data.csv", stringsAsFactors = F, 
    sep = ","))

Create folds

k = 10
k_loo = length(unique(exec_lhq$participant))

exec_lhq <- fold(exec_lhq, k = k, id_col = "participant") %>% ungroup()

exec_lhq <- fold(exec_lhq, k = k_loo, id_col = "participant") %>% ungroup()
## Warning in fold(exec_lhq, k = k_loo, id_col = "participant"): Found 1 existing
## fold column. It will NOT be replaced. Change 'handle_existing_fold_cols' to
## 'remove' if you want to replace it.
exec_lhq <- exec_lhq %>% rename(.folds10 = .folds_1, .folds.loo = .folds_2)

Entropy PCA and scaling of variables

exec_lhq_ppd <- preprocess_steps(exec_lhq)

Join LHQ and AXCPT

# Merge behavioral and subject data (restricting to only those in subject data
# frame)
axcpt_ppd <- left_join(axcpt, exec_lhq_ppd, by = "participant", suffix = c(".x", 
    ""))
axcpt_ppd <- axcpt_preprocess(axcpt_ppd)

sd.rt <- axcpt_ppd %>% group_by(participant) %>% summarise(meanRT = mean(RT_correct, 
    na.rm = T)) %>% ungroup()

sd.rt <- sd.rt %>% mutate(gmean = mean(meanRT), gsd = sd(meanRT), lower = gmean - 
    2.5 * gsd, upper = gmean + 2.5 * gsd, outlier = ifelse(meanRT >= lower & meanRT <= 
    upper, "fine", "outlier"))

sd.acc <- axcpt_ppd %>% group_by(participant) %>% summarise(meanAcc = mean(accuracy_target))

exclude <- sd.rt$participant[sd.rt$outlier == "outlier"]

axcpt_ppd <- axcpt_ppd[!(axcpt_ppd$participant %in% exclude), ]

exec_lhq_ppd <- exec_lhq_ppd[!(exec_lhq_ppd$participant %in% exclude), ]

exec_lhq_ppd <- fold(exec_lhq_ppd, k = k_loo - length(exclude), id_col = "participant", 
    handle_existing_fold_cols = "remove") %>% ungroup()

k_loo = k_loo - length(exclude)

exec_lhq_ppd <- exec_lhq_ppd %>% rename(.folds.loo = .folds)

newfolds <- exec_lhq_ppd %>% select(participant, .folds.loo)

axcpt_ppd <- axcpt_ppd %>% select(-.folds.loo)
axcpt_ppd <- axcpt_ppd %>% left_join(newfolds)
## Joining, by = "participant"

Jobs data

axcpt_ppd$occupation <- factor(axcpt_ppd$occupation)
contrasts(axcpt_ppd$occupation) <- contr.sum(4)

Experiment version

axcpt_ppd$ExperimentName <- factor(axcpt_ppd$ExperimentName)
contrasts(axcpt_ppd$ExperimentName) <- contr.sum(3)

Analysis 2: AXCPT GLMNET

axcpt_ppd <- axcpt_ppd[axcpt_ppd$Condition != "AX", ]
axcpt_ppd.rt <- axcpt_ppd[!is.na(axcpt_ppd$RT_correct), ]

10-fold cross-validation

RT

mm_rt = model.matrix(RT_correct ~ aoa * (Condition * L2_exposure + Condition * PCA_Work + 
    Condition * PCA_General), data = axcpt_ppd.rt)

axcpt.rt.lasso = cv.glmnet(x = mm_rt, y = axcpt_ppd.rt$RT_correct, type.measure = "mse", 
    parallel = T, foldid = as.numeric(axcpt_ppd.rt$.folds10))

axcpt.rt.lasso.error <- data.frame(lambda = axcpt.rt.lasso$lambda, cvm = axcpt.rt.lasso$cvm, 
    cvlo = axcpt.rt.lasso$cvlo, cvup = axcpt.rt.lasso$cvup, lambda.min = axcpt.rt.lasso$lambda.min, 
    lambda.1se = axcpt.rt.lasso$lambda.1se, error_metric = axcpt.rt.lasso$name)
## Warning in data.frame(lambda = axcpt.rt.lasso$lambda, cvm =
## axcpt.rt.lasso$cvm, : row names were found from a short variable and have been
## discarded
p1 <- axcpt.rt.lasso.error %>% ggplot(aes(x = log(lambda), y = cvm, ymin = cvlo, 
    ymax = cvup)) + geom_point(colour = "red") + geom_errorbar() + geom_vline(aes(xintercept = log(lambda.1se)), 
    linetype = 4) + geom_vline(aes(xintercept = log(lambda.min)), linetype = 3) + 
    theme_minimal(base_size = 12) + ylab(axcpt.rt.lasso$name) + xlab("Regularization parameter: log()") + 
    coord_cartesian(xlim = c(4.5, -3))
ggsave("figures/lasso_axcpt.rt_trial_error_10fold.png", width = 17.8, height = 11, 
    units = "cm")

p2 <- axcpt.rt.lasso$glmnet.fit %>% tidy() %>% filter(term != "(Intercept)") %>% 
    mutate(term = fct_reorder(term, str_length(term))) %>% ggplot(aes(log(lambda), 
    estimate, color = term)) + geom_line(size = 1.15) + geom_hline(yintercept = 0, 
    linetype = "solid") + geom_vline(xintercept = log(axcpt.rt.lasso$lambda.1se), 
    linetype = 4) + geom_vline(xintercept = log(axcpt.rt.lasso$lambda.min), linetype = 3) + 
    theme_minimal(base_size = 12) + guides(colour = guide_legend("Effect", ncol = 1)) + 
    ylab("Model estimate") + xlab("Regularization parameter: log()") + coord_cartesian(xlim = c(4.5, 
    -3))
ggsave("figures/lasso_axcpt.rt_trial_10fold.png", width = 17.8, height = 11, units = "cm")

(plot <- ggarrange(p1, p2, nrow = 2, labels = c("A", "B"), common.legend = T, legend = "right", 
    align = "v"))
ggsave(plot = plot, file = "figures/lasso_axcpt_rt_trial_10fold_2row.png", width = 17.8, 
    height = 22.5, units = "cm")

LOO cross-validation

RT

mm_rt = model.matrix(RT_correct ~ aoa * (Condition * L2_exposure + Condition * PCA_Work + 
    Condition * PCA_General), data = axcpt_ppd.rt)

axcpt.rt.lasso = cv.glmnet(x = mm_rt, y = axcpt_ppd.rt$RT_correct, type.measure = "mse", 
    parallel = T, foldid = as.numeric(axcpt_ppd.rt$.folds.loo), standardize = T)

axcpt.rt.lasso.error <- data.frame(lambda = axcpt.rt.lasso$lambda, cvm = axcpt.rt.lasso$cvm, 
    cvlo = axcpt.rt.lasso$cvlo, cvup = axcpt.rt.lasso$cvup, lambda.min = axcpt.rt.lasso$lambda.min, 
    lambda.1se = axcpt.rt.lasso$lambda.1se, error_metric = axcpt.rt.lasso$name)
## Warning in data.frame(lambda = axcpt.rt.lasso$lambda, cvm =
## axcpt.rt.lasso$cvm, : row names were found from a short variable and have been
## discarded
p1 <- axcpt.rt.lasso.error %>% ggplot(aes(x = log(lambda), y = sqrt(cvm), ymin = sqrt(cvlo), 
    ymax = sqrt(cvup))) + geom_point(colour = "red") + geom_errorbar() + geom_vline(aes(xintercept = log(lambda.1se)), 
    linetype = 4, size = 1) + geom_vline(aes(xintercept = log(lambda.min)), linetype = 3, 
    size = 1) + theme_minimal(base_size = 12) + ylab("RMSE") + xlab("Regularization parameter: log()") + 
    coord_cartesian(xlim = c(4.5, -3))
ggsave("figures/lasso_axcpt.rt_trial_error_loo.png", width = 17.8, height = 11, units = "cm")


terms <- axcpt.rt.lasso$glmnet.fit %>% tidy() %>% filter(term != "(Intercept)") %>% 
    mutate(term = str_replace(term, "Condition", "TrialType")) %>% mutate(term = fct_reorder(term, 
    str_length(term))) %>% select(term)
terms <- levels(terms$term)
pal <- rep("#A9A9A9", length(terms))

# ConditionAX, CondiitonAY, ConditionBY, PCA_Work, PCA_General, aoa:PCA_Work,
# aoa:PCA_General These colors are hacked together by hand. If you run some other
# model and the effects change they the coloring won't be accurate. Sorry!

pal <- data.frame(terms, pal, stringsAsFactors = F)
pal$pal[pal$term == "TrialTypeAY"] <- brewer.pal(n = 4, name = "Set1")[1]
pal$pal[pal$term == "TrialTypeBY"] <- brewer.pal(n = 4, name = "Set1")[3]
pal$pal[pal$term == "PCA_Work"] <- brewer.pal(n = 4, name = "Set1")[4]

pal$pal[pal$term == "TrialTypeAY:L2_exposure"] <- brewer.pal(n = 4, name = "Set1")[4]
pal$pal[pal$term == "TrialTypeAY:PCA_General"] <- brewer.pal(n = 4, name = "Set1")[4]
pal$pal[pal$term == "TrialTypeBY:PCA_General"] <- brewer.pal(n = 4, name = "Set1")[4]
pal$pal[pal$term == "aoa:PCA_Work"] <- brewer.pal(n = 4, name = "Set1")[4]
pal$pal[pal$term == "aoa:PCA_General"] <- brewer.pal(n = 4, name = "Set1")[4]

p2 <- axcpt.rt.lasso$glmnet.fit %>% tidy() %>% filter(term != "(Intercept)") %>% 
    mutate(term = str_replace(term, "Condition", "TrialType")) %>% mutate(term = fct_reorder(term, 
    str_length(term))) %>% ggplot(aes(log(lambda), estimate, group = term, colour = term)) + 
    geom_line(size = 1.15) + geom_hline(yintercept = 0, linetype = "solid") + geom_vline(xintercept = log(axcpt.rt.lasso$lambda.1se), 
    linetype = 4, size = 1) + geom_vline(xintercept = log(axcpt.rt.lasso$lambda.min), 
    linetype = 3, size = 1) + theme_minimal(base_size = 12) + guides(colour = guide_legend("Effect", 
    ncol = 1)) + ylab("Model estimate") + xlab("Regularization parameter: log()") + 
    coord_cartesian(xlim = c(4.5, -3)) + scale_color_manual(values = pal$pal)
ggsave("figures/lasso_axcpt.rt_trial_loo.png", width = 17.8, height = 11, units = "cm")

L2 Accent

accent_mm <- model.matrix(meanAccent ~ aoa * L2_exposure + aoa * PCA_General + aoa * 
    PCA_Work, data = exec_lhq_ppd)

accent.lasso = cv.glmnet(x = accent_mm, y = exec_lhq_ppd$meanAccent, type.measure = "mse", 
    parallel = T, foldid = as.numeric(exec_lhq_ppd$.folds.loo))
## Warning: Option grouped=FALSE enforced in cv.glmnet, since < 3 observations per
## fold
accent.lasso.error <- data.frame(lambda = accent.lasso$lambda, cvm = accent.lasso$cvm, 
    cvlo = accent.lasso$cvlo, cvup = accent.lasso$cvup, lambda.min = accent.lasso$lambda.min, 
    lambda.1se = accent.lasso$lambda.1se, error_metric = accent.lasso$name)

p1 <- accent.lasso.error %>% ggplot(aes(x = log(lambda), y = sqrt(cvm), ymin = sqrt(cvlo), 
    ymax = sqrt(cvup))) + geom_point(colour = "red") + geom_errorbar() + geom_vline(aes(xintercept = log(lambda.1se)), 
    linetype = 4) + geom_vline(aes(xintercept = log(lambda.min)), linetype = 3) + 
    theme_minimal(base_size = 12) + ylab("RMSE") + xlab("Regularization parameter: log()") + 
    coord_cartesian(xlim = c(0, -6))
ggsave("figures/lasso_accent_error_loo.png", width = 17.8, height = 11, units = "cm")
